Sure, here are some examples of how the word "zlo" can be used in different forms and positions in Serbian:

1. *Zlo* ne spava. (Evil never sleeps.)
2. Sinoć sam doživela *zlo*. (Last night I experienced something bad.)
3. On ne radi to iz *zla*. (He doesn't do it out of malice.)
4. *Zlo* se vraća kao bumerang. (Evil comes back like a boomerang.)
5. Nemoj da radiš *zlo* drugima. (Don't do harm to others.)
6. *Zlo* je već učinjeno. (The damage is already done.)
7. Ona je osoba puna *zla*. (She is a person full of evil.)
8. *Zlo* mi je od ovog filma. (This movie makes me sick.)
9. U svakom čoveku ima *zla* i dobra. (There is both good and evil in every person.)
10. Bez *zla* nema ni dobra. (There is no good without evil.)

I hope these examples help you understand the different ways "zlo" can be used in Serbian!